Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.41,0:00:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and Gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.69,0:00:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, for your pleasure, we present to you, \Na Christmas tale with a tint of drama: {/a little bit sad}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.80,0:00:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Jeremy's Tree."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.82,0:00:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear grandfathers, grandmothers, \Npapas, mamas, and, of course children!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.46,0:00:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even those who came on their own\Nare welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.58,0:00:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, let's get started now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.78,0:00:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.33,0:00:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.96,0:01:12.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(800,200)\c&HFAFEFD&\bord0.1\blur5\b0\fnEraser\fs50\pos(265,60)\3c&H353B6B&} Jeremy's Tree
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.05,0:01:18.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)\b0\fs30\c&HFFFFFF&\blur5\bord0.5\3c&H1F2149&\pos(265,160)} Original work by Iruka {原作}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, when December finally comes, \NI become by all means twitchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.48,0:01:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Christmas month \Nis also my birthday month.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.64,0:01:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even a Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.79,0:01:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet, every Christmas eve{/day}, I offer a prayer \Nof gratitude for the happiness of being alive. {lit is "I am doing gratitude/thanks" and i've no clue what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.72,0:01:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But also, I pray that we don't forget \Nthat there are countless people and creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.47,0:01:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,stricken with sadness, \Nunder this very same sky. {lit: I think we can't forget that there are many people and living beings thinking sad thoughts}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.68,0:02:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be nicer if everyone was happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.63,0:02:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This story you're about to see - Jeremy's tree \Nis the materialization of this pious wish of mine. {lit: jeremy's tree is a story I made by putting in that wish}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.51,0:02:36.84,Song,,0,0,0,,Powdered snow is falling on the flowers in the field {couldn't find any lyrics for this one so basing this solely around the wisper's output}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.72,0:02:45.61,Song,,0,0,0,,Let's go play around together, \Nbecause it's a wonderful Christmas eve, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.20,0:02:49.11,Song,,0,0,0,,Wave your hand, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.82,0:02:57.61,Song,,0,0,0,,When you break into a run, \Nthe morning sun glitters on your hair
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:05.95,Song,,0,0,0,,All the time, I keep hearing it -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.86,0:03:13.72,Song,,0,0,0,,Mama's voice from the long-long past
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.72,0:03:16.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, hold your head high {to throw out one's chest; to be puffed up with pride - could be it's what he hears mom's voice saying, then it's probably something less extreme and boastful, like simple "straighten your back"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.28,0:03:18.78,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:21.15,Song,,0,0,0,,with a smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:26.35,Song,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go, hit it with a bouncy step
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.57,0:03:35.81,Song,,0,0,0,,Keep going always straight ahead, \Nwithout ever looking back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:42.68,Song,,0,0,0,,However, if you see someone crying, \Nthere's no shame doing that {/in looking back}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:46.34,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, hold your head high
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.01,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.42,0:03:50.18,Song,,0,0,0,,with a smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.18,0:03:55.75,Song,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go, hit it with a bouncy step
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.73,0:04:01.17,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)} Wherever you go, bouncy step...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.47,0:04:04.56,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)} Wherever you go, bouncy step...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.02,0:04:09.58,Song,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go, walk with a bouncy step...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.55,0:04:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A wizard's Christmas cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.72,0:04:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.78,0:04:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.66,0:04:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing with that cake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.46,0:04:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.67,0:05:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,After I shook it up like this,\NI can no longer return it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.70,0:05:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys! Anyone's hungry here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Bon appetit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.78,0:05:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, about time we begin the Christmas party!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.63,0:05:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.32,0:06:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor thing. She's chilled to the marrow. {it's a girl later}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.28,0:06:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.88,0:06:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell me, where'd you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here flying from a faraway forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,From the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.64,0:06:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.51,0:06:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to find the fir tree \Nthat I spent my whole life with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.04,0:06:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The fir tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.62,0:06:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep inside the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,spreading out its green branches \Nin all directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.09,0:06:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it is ever so gently \Nwatching over all of us, the fir tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:07:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, it was like a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Back when I was little, I suddenly found myself \Nall alone in the nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.18,0:07:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite that, \NI've not been feeling one bit lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.64,0:08:15.71,Song,,0,0,0,,Felled in the forest, fir tree {woohoo, I found lyrics: https://ameblo.jp/yurara887/entry-12224599054.html} {切りたおされた　樅の木よ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.71,0:08:23.31,Song,,0,0,0,,The silver stars are an illusion {/but a beautiful lie } {no clue what this means: 銀の星は　まがいもの}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:31.79,Song,,0,0,0,,They don't suit you, not one bit {おまえには　似合わない}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.79,0:08:37.83,Song,,0,0,0,,But they do suit me... {私が似合う - no clue again, could be "but I suit you/them"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.08,0:08:43.37,Song,,0,0,0,,Standing still,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:47.39,Song,,0,0,0,,my fir tree, ah... {立ちつくす　樅の木よ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.39,0:08:55.08,Song,,0,0,0,,Tell me, do you still remember it - that forest? {憶えているか　あの森を}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.08,0:09:06.96,Song,,0,0,0,,Where me and you slept away those long dark nights... {黒い夜には　私と眠った}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:37.47,Song,,0,0,0,,Felled in the forest, fir tree {it's no longer technically in the forest but w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.56,0:09:45.53,Song,,0,0,0,,At last, I came to meet with you {私はやって来た}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.53,0:09:52.94,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll follow you, my beloved dear, {いとおしい　おまえのため}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:59.92,Song,,0,0,0,,Even in the hereafter {hades; realm of the dead; the next world​} {黄泉の国までも} {/Even into the next world }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.64,0:10:09.00,Song,,0,0,0,,Come back to life, my fir tree! {よみがえれ　樅の木よ}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.55,0:10:15.81,Song,,0,0,0,,Your branches are still in the prime of youth {おまえの枝は　わかざかり}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:28.14,Song,,0,0,0,,While the flames keep blinking... {炎がまばたき　する間に}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to return home \Nat least a single branch of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.97,0:10:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to live once more \Ntogether with it in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.16,0:10:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure is one heartbreaking story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.28,0:10:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The fir tree that you so cherished, \Nchopped off like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.03,0:10:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I know what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.87,0:11:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll both look for that precious fir tree of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.32,0:11:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Is that your tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.38,0:11:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one? Is this the tree we're looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.06,0:11:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.04,0:11:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be this fir either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one luxurious mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.80,0:11:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet they've got a splendiferous \NChristmas tree too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.58,0:12:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.43,0:12:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my first time seeing a party that dazzling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.92,0:12:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! There's the fir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.01,0:12:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks similar to my forest's fir...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.03,0:12:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Try calling it. {/crying/singing/tweeting}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the fir you're looking for, \Nit'll surely react!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fir from my forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.00,0:12:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask if we can have \Nat least one branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.67,0:12:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's a small bird, \Nwho needs that fir tree you got... {/who was looking for }
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.35,0:12:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.18,0:12:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tightwads! {/you stingy}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.15,0:12:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Like small kids! {has to be "赤ん坊" or "baby; infant" but I don't see what it may mean here}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.13,0:13:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if I try asking once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.84,0:13:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,After we went through all this trouble... {lit: after all, we managed to meet with it at last}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.38,0:13:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... The lights are out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.67,0:13:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do, Jeremy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.22,0:13:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing what Santa Claus does. {/imitate}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.11,0:13:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that the chimney is not an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.93,0:13:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.23,0:13:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like they forgot to lock it. {lit is "turn the key" but I don't suppose you'd lock a window with a key}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.15,0:13:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.92,0:14:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our fir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.89,0:14:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A branch!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.20,0:14:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The fir gifted you one of its twigs. {/small branch}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Christmas tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.82,0:14:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Rats!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.91,0:15:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.04,0:15:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.59,0:15:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.96,0:15:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.96,0:15:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.54,0:15:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, you can't die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You silly thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.94,0:15:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I be dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.69,0:15:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.50,0:15:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.95,0:15:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was for me that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.70,0:15:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:16:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you got to meet that fir,\Nit's all that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.89,0:16:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could go to the forest with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.16,0:16:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.56,0:16:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy... Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Santa Claus!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.10,0:16:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Santa... {/grandpa}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.60,0:16:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I have this fir twig... {no clue what he means to say: "I want/I have/etc" assumed he means to say "I want [to carry into the forest] this twig" as it is later}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.10,0:16:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I know all about that, Jeremy. {again, no clue what he understands}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No need. No need to explain. {still no clue, could be "agreed, I will grant [your wish]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.61,0:16:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what should I present our Jeremy with?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.20,0:16:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to fly away \Nto carry this twig back to the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.20,0:16:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! Want to go to the forest, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.81,0:16:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid, splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.31,0:16:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly feel so drowsy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.45,0:17:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep tight, Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.10,0:17:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time you open your eyes, \Nyou'll be in the forest already! {/wake up}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.76,0:17:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people are frolicking around, \Nlike powdery snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.24,0:17:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of that encounter on a city corner, {this lines seems to lead nowhere so as the next one, hence I'm artificially including some message/sense into it}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.54,0:17:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,between a small bird, looking for a fir tree \Nand a young boy, living all by himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.56,0:18:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,on that Christmas night, deep inside the forest, \Nthe boy settled down for an eternal sleep. {/fell asleep forever}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.55,0:18:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After some winters passed, \Na fir tree had sprouted from that spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.38,0:18:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,gradually growing big and strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, a great many \Nof small birds have made pilgrimage to that place,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.17,0:18:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where tenderly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,tenderly, they sing it \Nthe sweetest lullaby ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.62,0:18:39.35,Song,,0,0,0,,Friends from the Beech Forest, {ブナの森の仲間たち}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.03,0:18:47.07,Song,,0,0,0,,Have you all gone to sleep already? {もうみんな眠りましたか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.62,0:18:54.31,Song,,0,0,0,,Tell me, o wise Grandfather Moss, {なんじゃもんじゃごけのおじいさん - no clue what's the hidden meaning behind addressing some specific moss for it and calling it by full name; the word "nanjamonjagoke" is one of those in japanese that sound just like that thing they denote - mushi so maybe it's some playful silly form of a tongue-twister for children? I suspect that this moss is already a part of some other japanese fairy tale/folklore; also this is technically "grandpa of moss" so could be some even higher being, like the yokai that created everything in the forest?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.99,0:19:02.35,Song,,0,0,0,,The sad story of love of Princess Nettle {悲しい恋をしたいらくさ姫の}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.35,0:19:08.81,Song,,0,0,0,,If only you know this old legend, \Nwill you tell it to me? {伝説 知っていますか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:19.19,Song,,0,0,0,,This is my favorite lullaby \Nbefore going to sleep {ぼくが大好きなおやすみ前の子守唄}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.68,0:19:47.43,Song,,0,0,0,,When I open my eyes, \Nit'll be a brand new day {目が覚めたら明日こそ} {/tomorrow}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.01,0:19:54.91,Song,,0,0,0,,Let's go to faraway towns, \Nmeet the people there {遠くの町の人々に}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:20:01.53,Song,,0,0,0,,Would they be happy \Nif we brought them a bouquet of herbs? {ハーブの花束届けましょう} {was "ハーヴ" originally but has to be ハーブ}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.14,0:20:09.67,Song,,0,0,0,,Maybe the thorns in their hearts would then peel away {心の棘がぬける様に}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.67,0:20:15.98,Song,,0,0,0,,From somewhere, I hear the ringing of sheep bells {どこかで聞こえるひつじの鈴の音}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:26.15,Song,,0,0,0,,Even the wind had already fallen asleep - \Nsee you tomorrow {/until tomorrow} {風も眠ってしまったから 又あした}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.42,0:20:37.30,Song,,0,0,0,,As the moonlight blankets me gently, I will sleep. {月の光をあびながら眠ります}
